version.description:
Released in October 2010, Unicode 6.0 was the first version of the Unicode Standard to support emoji.

Some characters in prior versions of Unicode were retroactively updated to provide an emoji presentation. This release was the first to introduce new characters for the sole purpose of compatability with emojis being used in Japan.

emoji_net_data.category: Miscellaneous Symbols And Pictographs -> Comic style symbols
emoji_net_data.definition: An arm flexing to show its biceps muscle. Represents strength, or working out. Flexed Biceps was approved as part of Unicode 6.0 in 2010 and http://emojipedia.org/flexed-biceps/

apple_vendor_description: The flexed biceps emoji on Apple devices is a vibrant and powerful symbol of strength and achievement, rendered with striking glossy 3D shading that makes the muscle bulge appear almost tangible. Realistic lighting accentuates the curve and definition, while the smooth gradients contribute to its polished, energetic look. This emoji on Apple devices is universally understood to signify power, success, effort, or a feeling of accomplishment, often used to celebrate a victory or express determination.
